LGTM, thanks again @xiaohu2015 for the awesome contribution.

@jdsgomes thanks as well for your support and guidance.

I think we are good to merge. Just make sure we remove the unnecessary expect files `ModelTester.test_swin_*_expect.pk` for variants s/b/l that were removed.

✔️ 
@AlbertoEAF Many thanks for addressing all my comments so fast!
Unfortunately, I don't think I'm qualified to formally approve this PR, so I'm leaving my approval in a form of comment.

@max0x7ba thanks a bunch for this! this is great.

Would it be possible to add a small unit test for this?

If you give me the rough gist of the test I can take care of hooking it into the CI, etc.

Thanks for the PR @aabkn , the changes make sense (although I'm not qualified enough to do a full review). I left a few comments.

I'm curious if https://github.com/scrapinghub/number-parser integration might be useful. Also from the changes it looks like you're parsing free-form text with numbers spelled out as words, is this correct? I'm curious what is the usecase - it might help motivate the number-parser integration better.

@noviluni do you think it makes sense to check performance impact here?

@cojenco I'm not sure how this PR addresses #653 or #134.  The current behavior is that if the user does *not* pass an explicit project, the constructor falls back to inferring the project from the credentials / environment, but if the user passes an explicit `None` for the project, the constructor remembers that fact, preventing its accidental use when calling `Client.create_bucket` or `Client.list_buckets`.  For the rationale, see https://github.com/googleapis/google-cloud-python/issues/4239.

The two referenced bugs are both about failures to find the project ID in the credentials inferred from the environment, and thus won't be affected by this change at all.

Removing the client-side validation from `Client.create_bucket` / `Client.list_buckets` shouldn't hurt anything:  the [`buckets.insert`](https://cloud.google.com/storage/docs/json_api/v1/buckets/insert) and [`buckets.list`](https://cloud.google.com/storage/docs/json_api/v1/buckets/list) APIs will both raise exceptions if `project` is not passed.

@GhBlg I pushed to your branch with some minor formatting/parameter name change. :)

I also added `drop_prob` param in the `TC_block` definition part to match the original implementation.

I am happy with the changes, thanks for the effort @GhBlg!
